item.title: How old can a man have a baby?
item.description: Unlike women, who are born with a finite number of eggs, men continue to produce sperm throughout their life, and some can father children into their 60s and beyond — an age where women's clocks have totally stopped ticking. George Lucas, Steve Martin and Rod Stewart all famously fathered children in their late 60s. What is the maximum age for a man to have a baby? There is no set age-related limit on male fertility, though sperm quality declines slightly as a male ages.

item.title: Power Consumption - The Intel SSD DC S3700 (200GB) Review
item.description: Power Consumption Intel's SSD DC S3700 can draw power on both 12V or 5V rails.
